DOCUMENT();
############################################################ # Load Macros ############################################################ loadMacros( "PGstandard.pl", "PGML.pl", "AnswerFormatHelp.pl", "contextFiniteSolutionSets.pl", "contextForm.pl", "PGcourse.pl", ); COMMENT('Authored in PreTeXt');
############################################################ # Header ############################################################ TEXT(beginproblem());
############################################################ # PG Setup Code ############################################################ Context("FiniteSolutionSets"); Context()->variables->are(H=>'Real'); $answer = Formula("{8/7}");
############################################################ # Body ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML Solve the equation [`\frac{7H}{12}=\frac{2}{3}`] for [`H\text{.}`]
[_]{$answer}{10}
END_PGML
############################################################ # Solution ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION The left side is effectively the same thing as [`\frac{7}{12}H\text{,}`] so multiplying by [`\frac{12}{7}`] will isolate [`H\text{.}`]
[```\newcommand{\multiplyleft}[2][\cdot]{{\highlight{{#2#1{}}}}}\newcommand{\amp}{&} \begin{aligned} \frac{7H}{12}\amp=\frac{2}{3}\\ \multiplyleft{\left(\frac{12}{7}\right)}\left(\frac{7H}{12}\right)\amp=\multiplyleft{\left(\frac{12}{7}\right)}\frac{2}{3}\\ \left(\frac{\cancel{12}}{\bcancel{7}}\right)\left(\frac{\bcancel{7}H}{\cancel{12}}\right)\amp=\left(\frac{\cancelto{4}{12}}{7}\right)\frac{2}{\cancel{3}}\\ H\amp=\frac{8}{7} \end{aligned} ```]
We should check the solution by substituting [`\frac{8}{7}`]in for [`H`] in the original equation:
[```\newcommand{\substitute}[1]{{\color{blue}{{#1}}}}\newcommand{\confirm}[1]{\stackrel{\checkmark}{#1}}\newcommand{\wonder}[1]{\stackrel{\text{?}}{#1}}\newcommand{\amp}{&} \begin{aligned} \frac{7H}{12}\amp=\frac{2}{3}\\ \frac{7\left(\substitute{\frac{8}{7}}\right)}{12}\amp\wonder{=}\frac{2}{3}\\ \frac{8}{12}\amp\wonder{=}\frac{2}{3}\\ \frac{2}{3}\amp\confirm{=}\frac{2}{3} \end{aligned} ```]
The solution [`\frac{8}{7}`] is checked, and the solution set is [`\left\{\frac{8}{7}\right\}\text{.}`]
END_PGML_SOLUTION
